payload.text:
To integrate all the functionalities from the legacy `index` files (Incidentes, Exploits, Zero Days, CVEs, Alertas, Fuentes, Mitigaciones), I will create a **Generic Resource Manager**.

Instead of creating 7 nearly identical components, I will build one robust `ResourceManager` component that takes a "configuration" (columns, form fields, storage keys) and dynamically generates the UI and logic for each tab.

Here is the implementation plan:

1.  **`types.ts`**: Add interfaces for the new data models.
2.  **`services/api.ts`**: Add generic CRUD functions and initial mock data for these new modules.
3.  **`components/ResourceManager.tsx`**: A new, powerful component that handles listing, searching, creating, editing, and deleting data based on configuration.
4.  **`App.tsx`**: Define the configuration for each module (Incidents, CVEs, etc.) and render the `ResourceManager` when those tabs are active.

# Updated files:

## types.ts

```typescript
export interface NewsItem {
  title: string;
  feedTitle: string;
  link: string;
  pubDate: string;
  description?: string;
}

export type RiskPriority = 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';
export type RiskStatus = 'detectado' | 'notificado' | 'mitigando' | 'resuelto' | 'riesgo-aceptado';

export interface ActivityLog {
  type: 'comment' | 'status_change';
  timestamp: number;
  text?: string;
  status?: string;
  comment?: string;
}

export interface RiskTicket {
  id: number;
  title: string;
  customers: string[];
  tags: string[];
  priority: RiskPriority;
  description: string;
  status: RiskStatus;
  createdAt: number;
  lastUpdated: number;
  activity: ActivityLog[];
}

// --- New Data Models for OSINT Brief Modules ---

export interface Incident {
  id: string;
  date: string;
  type: string;
  entity: string;
  country: string;
  sector: string;
  description: string;
  compromisedData: string;
  actor: string;
  url?: string;
}

export interface Exploit {
  id: string;
  date: string;
  name: string;
  type: string;
  platform: string;
  cve?: string;
  url?: string;
}

export interface ZeroDay {
  id: string;
  zdId: string; // e.g., ZDI-2024-123
  date: string;
  name: string;
  platform: string;
  cvss: number;
  status: string; // Activo, Mitigado, etc.
  description: string;
  url?: string;
}

export interface CVE {
  id: string;
  cveId: string;
  date: string;
  app: string;
  cvss: number;
  status: string;
  description: string;
  url?: string;
}

export interface Alert {
  id: string;
  date: string;
  title: string;
  severity: 'Informacional' | 'Baja' | 'Media' | 'Alta' | 'Critica';
  description: string;
  url?: string;
}

export interface IntelSource {
  id: string;
  date: string;
  name: string;
  type: string;
  description: string;
  url?: string;
}

export interface Mitigation {
  id: string;
  date: string;
  title: string;
  category: string;
  priority: 'Baja' | 'Media' | 'Alta';
  description: string;
  url?: string;
}

export type TabName = 
  | 'dashboard' 
  | 'incidentes' 
  | 'exploits' 
  | 'zerodays' 
  | 'cves' 
  | 'alertas' 
  | 'fuentes' 
  | 'mitigaciones' 
  | 'observatorio' 
  | 'riesgos';
```

